            "caption": "For founder Hazel Guo, the impetus to create Yoé was shaped by her own health struggles.",
            "heading": "",
            "text": "<p>For founder Hazel Guo, the impetus to create Yoé was shaped by her own health struggles. <br/>After being diagnosed with multiple autoimmune disorders in her early 20’s, she devoted herself to the pursuit of nutritional and lifestyle research. With the help of her doctors, rounds of elimination diets, and a committed meditation practice, Guo succeeded in getting most of her symptoms to a manageable level, but she couldn’t fully heal her newly reactive skin. A luxury beauty devotee at heart, Guo was dismayed to find that once-favorite products were no longer tolerable; at the same time, organic and natural brands often fell short on performance and sensorial elegance. Driven to create something wholly novel, she met with numerous experts in skincare formulation—an exhaustive search that led her to an Italian-born cosmetic chemist who serves as the brand’s chief scientist and formulator of the SynerGenius™complex.</p>",
